name: Example 2.0
description: CatBoost is a machine learning gradient-boosting library that builds decision trees optimized for handling categorical data with high accuracy and minimal data preprocessing.

name: CatBoost Classifier
description:
CatBoost is a high-performance open-source library for gradient boosting on decision trees that we can use for classification, regression and ranking tasks.

CatBoost uses a combination of ordered boosting, random permutations and gradient-based optimization to achieve high performance on large and complex data sets with categorical features.

name: Gemini 3 Pro
description: Gemini is a multimodal generative artificial intelligence chatbot and virtual assistant developed by Google. It is designed to understand and work with different types of information, including text, code, audio, image, and video.

name: Latent Dirichlet Allocation
description: Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA) is a key topic modeling technique in machine learning that discovers abstract "topics" within a collection of documents, representing each document as a mix of these hidden topics and each topic as a collection of related words, useful for organizing large text sets and understanding underlying themes. It works by assuming documents are generated from a random mixture of topics, and then reverses this process to find topic-word probabilities and document-topic proportions, effectively uncovering hidden themes like "sports" or "politics".

name: spaCy NLP Pipeline
description: The spaCy NLP pipeline is a sequence of components that process raw text and enrich it with linguistic annotations to produce a final Doc object. This process is central to how spaCy works, enabling various Natural Language Processing (NLP) tasks....

name: Graph Convolutional Network
description: Graph Convolutional Networks are neural networks designed specifically for graph-structured data. They leverage node relationships and graph topology to learn meaningful representations. GCNs are commonly used for node classification, link prediction, recommendation systems, and social network analysis.

name: Stable Diffusion
description: Stable Diffusion is a powerful text-to-image generative model that uses diffusion processes to transform random noise into detailed images guided by text prompts. It enables high-quality image synthesis with relatively low computational requirements compared to earlier generative models. Stable Diffusion is widely adopted for digital art, concept design, visual storytelling, and creative experimentation across various industries.

name: Latent Dirichlet Allocation
description: Latent Dirichlet Allocation is a probabilistic topic modeling technique that identifies hidden thematic structures within large collections of text documents. It is commonly used for document clustering, content recommendation, and exploratory text analysis in natural language processing.

name: Random Forest Classifier
description: Random Forest is an ensemble learning algorithm that builds multiple decision trees and combines their predictions to improve accuracy and robustness. By reducing overfitting and handling non-linear data effectively, it is widely used for classification and regression tasks in structured data analysis.

name: CLIP
description: CLIP is a multimodal model that learns associations between images and text using contrastive learning. It enables zero-shot learning by understanding visual concepts through language supervision. CLIP is widely used for image classification, retrieval, and cross-modal understanding tasks.

name: StyleGAN
description: StyleGAN is a generative adversarial network capable of synthesizing highly realistic human face images. It provides fine-grained control over visual attributes such as pose, lighting, and facial features. StyleGAN is widely used in research, entertainment, and creative media industries.

name: WaveNet
description: WaveNet is a deep generative model capable of producing highly realistic raw audio waveforms. It models audio signals directly, allowing it to generate natural-sounding speech and music. WaveNet is widely used in text-to-speech systems and audio synthesis applications.

name: DeepSpeech
description: DeepSpeech is an end-to-end deep learning model for automatic speech recognition that converts spoken language into written text. It is trained on large-scale speech datasets and is commonly used in voice assistants, transcription services, and accessibility technologies.

name: MobileNet
description: MobileNet is a lightweight convolutional neural network architecture optimized for mobile and embedded devices. It uses depthwise separable convolutions to reduce computation while maintaining accuracy. MobileNet is widely used in real-time applications such as object detection and image recognition on edge devices.

name: Transformer
description: The Transformer architecture is based entirely on self-attention mechanisms, eliminating the need for recurrent or convolutional layers. This design allows for efficient parallelization and better handling of long-range dependencies in sequences. Transformers form the foundation of modern NLP systems, including language models, translation systems, and summarization tools.

name: AlexNet
description: AlexNet is one of the earliest deep convolutional neural networks that demonstrated the effectiveness of deep learning for image classification. Its success in the ImageNet competition marked a turning point in computer vision research, leading to widespread adoption of neural networks for visual recognition tasks.

name: EfficientNet
description: EfficientNet is a family of convolutional neural networks that uses compound scaling to balance network depth, width, and resolution. This approach achieves higher accuracy with significantly fewer parameters and lower computational cost. EfficientNet models are widely used in production systems where performance, speed, and resource efficiency are critical factors.

name: VGG-16
description: VGG-16 is a deep convolutional neural network characterized by its simple and uniform architecture consisting of multiple stacked convolutional layers. Despite its computational cost, it remains a popular model for benchmarking and feature extraction. VGG-16 is frequently used in transfer learning scenarios for tasks such as image classification, object detection, and image segmentation.

name: ResNet-50
description: ResNet-50 is a deep convolutional neural network that introduces residual connections to solve the vanishing gradient problem in very deep architectures. By allowing gradients to flow directly through shortcut connections, it enables stable training of networks with dozens of layers. ResNet-50 is widely used for image classification, object detection, feature extraction, and as a backbone in many computer vision systems.

name: BERT
description: BERT (Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers) is a transformer-based language model designed to understand the contextual meaning of words by processing text bidirectionally. Unlike traditional language models that read text in one direction, BERT analyzes both the left and right context simultaneously, allowing it to capture deeper semantic relationships. It is widely used in natural language understanding tasks such as question answering, sentiment analysis, named entity recognition, text classification, and search ranking systems.

name: GPT-2
description: GPT-2 is a large-scale autoregressive language model trained to generate text by predicting the next word in a sequence. It is capable of producing long, coherent, and contextually relevant passages of text based on an initial prompt. GPT-2 is commonly used for text generation, conversational agents, summarization, creative writing, and language modeling research, demonstrating strong capabilities in unsupervised learning.
